Messages.Value: Thank you for calling XYZ Travel Agency. My name is Noah. How may I assist you today?

Hi Noah, my name is John Smith. I recently traveled to New York City and my luggage did not arrive with me. I filed a report with the airline, but I wanted to check if there is anything else I can do to track down my luggage. My flight details were with United Airlines, flight number UA234, departing from Atlanta on January 10th at 7:00 PM, arriving in JFK at 10:00 PM.
I'm sorry to hear that, John. Losing luggage can be very frustrating. I can certainly understand why you would be concerned. Let me check the status of your luggage for you.

According to our records, your luggage is still being tracked and has not yet been found. However, we will continue to actively search for it and will update you as soon as we have any new information. We apologize for the inconvenience and appreciate your patience.
Okay, thank you for your help, Noah.
Of course, John. Is there anything else I can assist you with?
No, that's all for now. I just wanted to check on my luggage. Thank you for your help.
You're welcome, John. Please don't hesitate to reach out if you have any further questions or concerns. Have a great day!
